# Supabase — leave blank to run local-first (localStorage + bootstrap/seed).
# When set, the app requires sign-in: email-OTP login gated to the org domain
# (@allincapital.vc), one shared live dashboard for the whole team.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# Server-only — never expose to the browser (API routes / scripts)
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# Auth — OTP emails sent via Resend (https://resend.com)
# Create an API key, verify your domain, then set a from address on that domain.
RESEND_API_KEY=
RESEND_FROM_EMAIL=FundOS <auth@allincapital.vc>
# Optional extra secret for hashing OTP codes (defaults to service role key)
# AUTH_OTP_SECRET=

# Ingest → document extraction backend. Bulk CSV/XLSX import needs none of these.
# Precedence: OpenRouter → Gemini → DeepSeek → Anthropic (first key set wins).
#
# OpenRouter (one key → Gemini & many vision models, NO Google project needed).
# Sign in at https://openrouter.ai → Keys → create (starts with sk-or-...).
# Reads scanned PDFs by OCR through a vision model. For hard scans you can set
# OPENROUTER_PDF_ENGINE=mistral-ocr (dedicated OCR) instead of the default native.
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# OPENROUTER_MODEL=google/gemini-2.5-flash
# OPENROUTER_PDF_ENGINE=native
#
# Gemini (BEST for scanned / poor-quality PDFs — reads them natively as OCR).
# Free tier + key at https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# Default model is gemini-flash-latest (auto-tracks current flash). For the
# worst scans set GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-pro-latest or gemini-3-pro-preview.
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-flash-latest
# GEMINI_BASE_URL=https://generativelanguage.googleapis.com/v1beta
#
# DeepSeek (cheapest, ~pennies) — https://platform.deepseek.com/
# TEXT ONLY: reads the text layer of PDFs + DOCX; it CANNOT OCR scans/images.
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=
# DEEPSEEK_BASE_URL=https://api.deepseek.com
# DEEPSEEK_MODEL=deepseek-chat
#
# Anthropic (native images/PDF, higher cost). Pick ONE:
#   • API key (simplest): set below, from https://console.anthropic.com/
#   • OAuth, no paid key: `ant auth login` (install: brew install anthropics/tap/ant),
#     then run the dev server with ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN exported:
#       export ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN=$(ant auth print-credentials --access-token)
# All are server-side only — never expose a credential to the browser.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Ingest → Google Drive picker (optional). Both are browser-exposed (NEXT_PUBLIC),
# so scope them tightly. Setup in Google Cloud Console (console.cloud.google.com):
#   1. Create/select a project. Enable "Google Picker API" and "Google Drive API".
#   2. OAuth consent screen → External → add your email as a Test user.
#   3. Credentials → Create OAuth client ID → Web application →
#      Authorized JavaScript origins: http://localhost:3000  → copy the Client ID.
#   4. Credentials → Create API key → copy it (optionally restrict to the two APIs).
# Docs export to PDF and Sheets to XLSX, then flow through the same review queue.
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=
NEXT_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_API_KEY=

# LP reporting emails (separate from OTP auth sender)
RESEND_LP_FROM_EMAIL=All In Capital <team@allincapital.vc>
